Indonesia Stocks: International Nickel, Sinar Mas Agro, United

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-09-16T09:11:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/indonesia-stocks-astra-sinar-mas-agro-international-nickel.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 60.85 points, or 1.6
percent, to 3,835.18, the first increase in six days. The gauge
has dropped 4.1 percent this week, the steepest weekly loss
since Aug. 5.  PT International Nickel  Indonesia  (INCO IJ), the nation’s
biggest producer of the metal, jumped 4.2 percent to 3,750
rupiah, ending a five-day slump. Nickel for three-month delivery
gained 2 percent to $21,800 metric ton on the London Metal
Exchange yesterday, and added 0.5 percent to $21,901 a ton at
4:02 p.m. Jakarta time.  PT Sinar Mas Agro Resources & Technology (SMAR IJ), a palm
oil producer known as PT SMART, climbed 2.3 percent to 6,650
rupiah. PT SMART said Nestle SA will resume  palm oil  purchases
from the company. Nestle stopped buying its palm oil from last
year after Greenpeace alleged the company was destroying
rainforest to make way for plantations.  PT United Tractors (UNTR IJ), Indonesia’s biggest heavy
equipment seller, advanced 2.6 percent to 23,500 rupiah, the
most since Sept. 5. United Tractors expects 2012 coal output to
rise 22 percent from this year to 5.5 million tons, Kontan
reported, citing Corporate Secretary Sara Loebis. Three calls to
the company’s office in Jakarta weren’t answered  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
